==English==

===Etymology===
From'' Arius'', afterwards Bishop of Nicomedia Circa 300.

====Noun====
'''Arianism'''

#Subscription to the  [[Arian Heresy]]. Arius reasoned that if [[Christ]] was the son of [[God]], He must be younger than God, and therefore less than God. Since God was [[eternal]] and Christ was not; therefore Christ was not wholly God. The heresy was [[scotch]]ed at the Council of Nicea in 325.

